President Obama congratulates the people of Albania on their country's 100th anniversary of independence. He emphasizes Albania's potential to strengthen its democracy, grow its economy, and continue necessary reforms to become a prominent European nation. The United States has had a long-standing alliance with Albania, dating back to its early years of independence and further reinforced after the fall of communism. The partnership between the two countries has been enhanced by the contributions of Albanian-Americans. President Obama assures Albania of the United States' continued support for the next hundred years and beyond.